data.description: The lone survivor of the India Air Force chopper crash, Group Captain Varun Singh battles on. A lot of people are praying for his speedy recovery. Varun Singh has suffered 40 percent burns and he is in critical condition. Times Now has exclusively talked to the father of Captain Varun Singh. Retired Colonel KP Singh said that as of now he doesn't have any information as the medical team hasn't contacted them. Watch the full video to know more. Listen in!
